Dele Ogunyemi The Ijaw Youth Council Worldwide has called on Nigerians  to protect themselves following  the rising security problems in the country. In a statement  by the President, IYC Worldwide, Pereotubo Oweilaemi, on Saturday, the group said Muhammadu Buhari regime had failed. He said, “The Federal Government has failed in its primary responsibility of securing lives and property in the country.” The group  however commended  South-West governors for setting up  Operation Amotekun and called on  the governors and leaders of the other zones  to replicate the same in their respective regions. Copyright PUNCH.
